in x^3+x-130=0, solve for the value for x
To solve this equation for x, you can use long division or a graphing calculator. 
One way to do it is by using long division:

7x + 25 = 0 (dividing both sides by 7)
1.43x = -25 (subtracting 7 from both sides)
x = -16.9 (multiplying both sides by 7 to undo the previous step)

So, x=−16.9 is one solution for the equation x^3+x-130=0.
